1 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
2 That Section(s) 11–101(a–4) and (c–6) through (c–12) of Article – Tax – General of the
3 Annotated Code of Maryland be renumbered to be Section(s) 11–101(a–5) and (c–8) through
4 (c–14), respectively.
5 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
6 as follows:
7 Article – Public Safety
8 5–101.
9 (a) In this subtitle the following words have the meanings indicated.
10 (h) (1) “Firearm” means:
11 (i) a weapon that expels, is designed to expel, or may readily be
12 converted to expel a projectile by the action of an explosive;
13 (ii) the frame or receiver of such a weapon; or
14 (iii) an unfinished frame or receiver, as defined in § 5–701 of this title.
15 (2) “Firearm” includes a starter gun.
16 5–133.1.
17 (a) In this section, “ammunition” means a cartridge, shell, or any other device
18 containing explosive or incendiary material designed and intended for use in a firearm.
19 Article – Tax – General
20 11–101.
21 (a) In this title the following words have the meanings indicated.
22 (A–4) “AMMUNITION” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 5–133.1 OF THE PUBLIC
23 SAFETY ARTICLE.
24 (C–6) “FIREARM” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 5–101 OF THE PUBLIC
25 SAFETY ARTICLE.
26 (C–7) “FIREARM ACCESSORY” MEANS:
27 (1) A MAGAZINE OR MAGAZINE LOADER;

